<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=97433599114289></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f97433599114289><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=6&mid=97433599114289>RE: lvl 16 need hunting areas</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=6&mid=97433599114289#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=2048><span id=Sage>SouldragoonFlamingheart</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>143 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Nov 15th 7:53 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>In a couple of levels, you'll be able to hit unrest for some outstanding loot.&nbsp;&nbsp;Go with Giddy's idea on the beetles till you hit 18.  They ARE a great source of exp.  You really don't have very far to go before 18.  Then take a ride out to gfay and get bound.  Once you learn the layout and the pathing of unrest, you shouldn't have a hard time reaping the bronze armor and fine steel weapon drops on alot of the mobs there.  I wrote an htm file on the bandit sashes at www.geocities.com/kingsofbrotherhood/members/Souldragoon/sashes.htm.  Somewhere in there, it says at what level the bandits stop agroing when you fight them.  I think it's 22.. when you can pick and fight a bandit and not worry about the other bandits joining in the fight.  Bandit sashes will start flowin, as well as the bronze that the bandits drop.  I made enough money at 22, doing the sashes, to keep me financially satisfied for many levels afterwards.<br><br>Souldragoon Flamingheart<br>40th circle Paladin of Virtue<br>Fennin Ro<br>&nbsp;<br><i>Follow virtue, and the virtuous will follow you.</i></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
